Description. Colony encrusting. Autozooids rectangular to irregularly pentagonal (c. 0.5 × 0.4 mm ;
Table 5
). Frontal shield flattened to slightly convex with large, round, regularly spaced pseudopores (average 89 per zooid), separated by approximately the width of a pseudopore, extending to zooid borders; interzooidal boundaries marked by slightly elevated rims, marginal areolar pores large to very large, some triangular.

Ovicell recumbent upon frontal shield of distal zooid, not crossed by suture lines, approximately circular (c. 0.3 × 0.3 mm ). Orifice dimorphism not distinctive but ovicellate orifices slightly wider than autozooidal orifices (c. 0.16 mm vs 0.15 mm ;
Table 5
).
